# .mastignore -- paths excluded from `mast` spec discovery.
#
# One path prefix or glob per line; lines starting with '#' and blank lines
# are ignored. A trailing '/' matches a directory and everything under it.
# `mast` walks from this directory and skips anything matched here, so vendored
# code, build output, and nested mast projects never pollute the corpus.
#
# Uncomment or add entries as needed:
# target/
# node_modules/
# vendor/
# examples/
